# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# PETALS & FLORA - FRONTEND ENVIRONMENT CONFIGURATION
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env and fill in the values for your environment
# NEVER commit .env to version control - it contains sensitive data
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─── API CONFIGURATION ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Backend API base URL
# Development: http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/
# Production: https://your-api-domain.com/api/
# IMPORTANT: Use HTTPS in production
REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/

# Optional explicit Django admin host when the admin lives on a different domain
# Example: https://your-backend-domain.com/admin/
REACT_APP_DJANGO_ADMIN_BASE_URL=

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECURITY BEST PRACTICES
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# 1. API URL:
#    - MUST use HTTPS in production
#    - Should be a full domain, not localhost
#    - Environment variables are embedded in the build, so they should not
#      contain truly sensitive information (use server-side logic for that)
#
# 2. Environment Variables:
#    - Frontend env vars are embedded in the bundle - keep them non-sensitive
#    - Never put API keys, tokens, or secrets here
#    - Use backend for sensitive operations
#
# 3. Build Command:
#    - Run: npm run build
#    - Output is in build/ directory
#    - These are static files served by your web server
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
